0.1.1.author: Takamitsu Endo
0.1.1.name: CollidingCombSynth
0.1.1.description: CollidingCombSynth is an experimental synthesizer which sounds like bowed string. Equipped with 24 Karplus-Strong string models which collide to each other. Tuning of pitch is possible, but difficult. So mostly suitable for sound effects.

0.1.10.author: Takamitsu Endo
0.1.10.name: CubicPadSynth
0.1.10.description: CubicPadSynth is a wavetable synthesizer which uses PADsynth algorithm to generate oscillator tables. Cubic interpolation is used to get smooth sound even at inaudible low frequency range. LFO waveform can be directly drawn.

0.1.11.author: Takamitsu Endo
0.1.11.name: EnvelopedSine
0.1.11.description: EnvelopedSine is an additive synthesizer that computes 64 sine waves for each note. Difference to IterativeSinCluster is that this synth has AD envelope and saturator for each oscillator. EnvelopedSine is better suited for percussive sounds.

0.1.12.author: Takamitsu Endo
0.1.12.name: IterativeSinCluster
0.1.12.description: IterativeSinCluster is an additive synthesizer. This synth computes 512 sine waves for each note to make tone cluster. I somehow thought "iterative sin" is a valid term. Correct term is "recursive sine".

0.1.8.author: Takamitsu Endo
0.1.8.name: LightPadSynth
0.1.8.description: LightPadSynth is a lightweight version of CubicPadSynth. For efficiency, interpolation is changed to linear. Also pitch modulation is omitted. Instead, a delay is added for each voice.

0.1.17.author: Takamitsu Endo
0.1.17.name: SyncSawSynth
0.1.17.description: SyncSawSynth is a 32 voice polyphonic synthesizer using up to 10th order PTR sawtooth oscillator. Just a basic synthesizer but very easy to make a noise similar to low battery sound of some toys.

0.1.13.author: Takamitsu Endo
0.1.13.name: TrapezoidSynth
0.1.13.description: TrapezoidSynth is a monophonic synthesizer equipped with 2 trapezoid oscillator. Trapezoid oscillator is based on PTR (Polynomial Transition Regions) and it has a drawback that increasing noise at high frequency. Therefore 8 times oversampled. 2 pitch shifters are added to make some chord.

2.1.0.author: discoDSP
2.1.0.name: OPL
2.1.0.description: OPL FM synth plugin emulates a digital sound synthesis chip developed by Yamaha in the mid 1980s

1.0.2.author: Jean Pierre Cimalando
1.0.2.name: ADLplug
1.0.2.description: FM synthesizer based on OPL3 and OPN2 sound chip emulations. Synthesis of melodic and percussive instruments, support for dynamic parameterization and automation.

1.0.2.author: Jean Pierre Cimalando
1.0.2.name: OPNplug
1.0.2.description: FM synthesizer based on OPL3 and OPN2 sound chip emulations. Synthesis of melodic and percussive instruments, support for dynamic parameterization and automation.

0.2.0.author: Artem Popov
0.2.0.name: Andes
0.2.0.description: Andes is a software synthesiser plugin in early stages of development. The core of Andes is an original oscillator which uses a pseudo-3D version of Perlin noise to produce distinctively digital sound.

2.4.0.author: Miguel Moreno
2.4.0.name: EP-MK1
2.4.0.description: Real-time physical model of an Electric Piano.

3.2.2.author: Paul Battersby
3.2.2.name: Virtual Playing Orchestra
3.2.2.description: Orchestral sample library featuring section and solo instruments for woodwinds, brass, strings and percussion

0.9.6.author: Pascal Gauthier
0.9.6.name: Dexed
0.9.6.description: Synthesizer closely modeled on the Yamaha DX7

1.0.0.author: Wolf Plugins
1.0.0.name: Wolf Spectrum
1.0.0.description: Spectrogram plugin which supports both log and linear frequency scaling

1.0.0.author: Filipe Coelho
1.0.0.name: Nekobi
1.0.0.description: Simple single-oscillator synth based on the Roland TB-303.

3.2.5.author: Michael Willis
3.2.5.name: Dragonfly Reverb
3.2.5.description: Dragonfly Reverb is a bundle of free audio effect plugins for Linux, MacOS, and Windows.

1.4.0.author: Resonant DSP
1.4.0.name: Swanky Amp
1.4.0.description: Tube amplifier simulation DSP plugin which aims to capture the details in the dynamics of tube amplifiers.

0.9.0.author: Matt Tytel
0.9.0.name: Helm
0.9.0.description: Polyphonic semi-modular synthesizer with a flexible modulation system.

3.0.0.author: Alexander Holm
3.0.0.name: Salamander Grand Piano
3.0.0.description: Yamaha C5, recorded with two AKG c414 disposed in an AB position ~12cm above the strings.

4.0.0.author: Brain Control
4.0.0.name: Tunefish
4.0.0.description: Tunefish is a tiny virtual analogue synth that was originally developed  for the 64k intros of the demo group Brain Control.

0.2.0.author: Clearly Broken
0.2.0.name: Ninjas 2
0.2.0.description: Easy to use sample slicer, quick slicing of sample and auto-mapping slices to midi note numbers.

2.1.0.author: Louis Gorenfeld
2.1.0.name: Digits
2.1.0.description: Digits is a phase distortion synthesizer inspired by Casio's CZ series but takes that form of synthesis to the limit. Create warm pads, glitchy sounds, dirty basses, filthy sweeps, screaming leads, and anything in-between.

2.4.0.author: discoDSP
2.4.0.name: OB-Xd
2.4.0.description: Based on the Oberheim OB-X. It attempts to recreate its sound and behaviours, but as the original was very limited in some important ways a number of things were added or altered to the original design. The OB-Xd was designed to sound as good and as rich as the original. It implements micro random detuning which is a big part of that sound.

1.0.0.author: Martin Eastwood
1.0.0.name: Mverb
1.0.0.description: Studio quality, open-source reverb. Its release was intended to provide a practical demonstration of Dattorro’s figure-of-eight reverb structure and provide the open source community with a high quality reverb.

2.2.4.author: TheWaveWarden
2.2.4.name: Odin
2.2.4.description: 12-voice polyphonic semi-modular synthesizer. Earth shattering basses, exquisite leads or mad FX, Odin's got them all! Use the classic sound of analog waveforms - or draw your own.

1.2.0.author: Chowdhury DSP
1.2.0.name: CHOW Matrix
1.2.0.description: Delay effect, made up of an infinitely growable tree of delay lines, each with individual controls for feedback, panning, distortion, and more.

1.9.0.author: Surge Synth Team
1.9.0.name: Surge
1.9.0.description: Hybrid synthesizer featuring many synthesis techniques, a great selection of filters, a flexible modulation engine, a smorgasbord of effects, and modern features like MPE and microtuning.

3.0.1.author: TAL Software
3.0.1.name: TAL-Filter
3.0.1.description: Host synced filter module with different filter types, panorama and volume modulation possibilities

5.0.4.author: TAL Software
5.0.4.name: TAL-Noisemaker
5.0.4.description: Virtual analog synthesizer with a great sound and low CPU usage.

2.4.0.author: TAL Software
2.4.0.name: TAL-Reverb
2.4.0.description: High quality plate reverb with a vintage 80's character

2.2.0.author: TAL Software
2.2.0.name: TAL-Vocoder
2.2.0.description: Vintage vocoder emulation with 11 bands that emulates the sound of vocoders from the early 80s

1.1.1.author: Paul Ferrand
1.1.1.name: Sfizz
1.1.1.description: SFZ parser and synth c++ library, providing AU / LV2 / VST3 plugins and JACK standalone client.
